Participant tested positive BZO. He did not admit to taking BZOs during the PSQ and when asked again about his medications on the PHQ, he reported taking Aleve, Tylenol & BC powder. Aleve (naproxen) can test false positive for BZO, so the protocol was continued. However, on the DUHQ, he admitted taking a Xanax last night, not prescribed, and has taken 20 pills in the last year. RG was notified and he approved to continue with protocol.
